In a quiet village, there was a large old tree standing in the middle of a field. For many years, it had seen storms, strong winds, hot summers, and cold winters.
One day, a young boy named Aman sat under the tree and asked his grandfather, "How does this tree stay so strong?"
The grandfather smiled and pointed at the tree.
"Look carefully," he said. "The tree bends when the wind is strong. It does not fight the storm. Its roots go deep into the ground, holding it steady."
Aman watched the branches moving gently with the wind.
"The tree teaches us something about life, "his grandfather continued. "Be flexible like the branches, strong like the roots, and patient like the seasons."
Aman looked at the tree agian.
It was quiet, simple, and beautiful yet full of wisdom.
And in that moment, he realized that somethimes the greatest teachers do not speak at all.
